message: What did you do in environmental policy?
Don’t mean to share a dystopian vision, but increasing human consumption is inevitable, so I worry that things like carbon sequestration won’t be enough

I’m also interested in environmental policy. I am fascinated by geo-engineering especially in regards to climate change. I feel like eliminating harmful emissions is an impossible goal and it will be orders of magnitude easier to reduce solar irradiance via more pollutants (ie sulfur dioxide).

Thank you for such a thoughtful and detailed answer. I’m happy to hear that the experience has been great. Did you apply specifically for the career change? What are you planning to do in the private sector?
And I did work in between! I was in dc doing environmental policy. I only worked in nonprofits and wanted to switch to the private sector, hence the b school move :p

Hi! I’m in between my first and second year now so I can’t quite speak yet to whether it’s been worth it :p but the summer has been great, and the business school experience has been incredible so far. It’s just so nice being back in school with all your friends living nearby :)
Hi Julia! I’ve been thinking about going back to school for an MBA. Did you work between undergrad and business school? And are you happy with where your degree has taken you?
